00:24:42,780 --> 00:24:43,110
Sorry.

578
00:24:43,110 --> 00:24:44,460
- We're sorry.
- Sorry.

579
00:24:44,630 --> 00:24:46,060
Different warden.

580
00:24:46,060 --> 00:24:46,700
Faster!

581
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:47,460
Sorry.

582
00:24:49,110 --> 00:24:50,220
My goodness.

583
00:24:50,430 --> 00:24:51,830
Different warden, but same attitude.

584
00:24:51,870 --> 00:24:52,700
Why does every warden

585
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:54,460
have to be so fierce?

586
00:24:59,150 --> 00:25:00,540
Don't you realize

587
00:25:01,220 --> 00:25:02,980
that when we talk about our story,

588
00:25:04,540 --> 00:25:06,190
love seems to come back a little?

589
00:25:10,460 --> 00:25:12,540
This is the movie we should be making.

590
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:15,540
Right.

591
00:25:23,830 --> 00:25:26,020
This is the movie we should make.

592
00:25:31,870 --> 00:25:33,060
Now, the script has changed,

593
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,590
the crew team has changed,

594
00:25:35,110 --> 00:25:36,830
and even the title.

595
00:25:39,350 --> 00:25:40,630
I didn't want to argue with them,

596
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:42,830
but I honestly didn't know what to do.

597
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:46,780
I'm sorry, Daji.

598
00:25:48,260 --> 00:25:49,110
I messed up.

599
00:25:57,220 --> 00:25:58,020
Zhou Shui,

600
00:25:58,870 --> 00:25:59,740
actually,

601
00:26:01,390 --> 00:26:03,190
I insisted on making this film

602
00:26:04,190 --> 00:26:07,260
to bring our love back.

603
00:26:09,430 --> 00:26:10,700
So no matter what happened

604
00:26:10,700 --> 00:26:12,390
or what Ms. Chao said to you,

605
00:26:12,830 --> 00:26:13,870
I told you to bear with it.

606
00:26:14,260 --> 00:26:15,260
I thought

607
00:26:16,460 --> 00:26:17,740
if we just held on,

608
00:26:17,740 --> 00:26:18,980
and the camera started rolling,

609
00:26:19,190 --> 00:26:20,220
we could decide everything

610
00:26:20,460 --> 00:26:22,190
as the directors.

611
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:24,780
But now,

612
00:26:25,390 --> 00:26:26,700
just like you said,

613
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:29,260
the script and the title

614
00:26:29,950 --> 00:26:30,950
have changed.

615
00:26:32,190 --> 00:26:33,870
It's no longer our story

616
00:26:34,950 --> 00:26:36,390
or our movie.

617
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:41,700
If you don't want to continue,

618
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:42,870
let's quit.

619
00:26:44,590 --> 00:26:45,630
I'll leave with you.

620
00:26:53,020 --> 00:26:54,630
I messed up.

621
00:26:55,340 --> 00:26:56,670
Ms. Chao didn't tell you to leave.

622
00:26:57,430 --> 00:26:59,300
You should stay and continue filming.

623
00:27:02,540 --> 00:27:04,150
Look, you forgot again.

624
00:27:05,740 --> 00:27:08,190
The most important thing
in a relationship is loyalty.

625
00:27:09,290 --> 00:27:11,260
I won't let you down,
and you won't let me down.

626
00:27:12,670 --> 00:27:14,500
If we're making it,
we're doing it together.

627
00:27:15,260 --> 00:27:16,630
If not, we leave together.

628
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,670
But if we don't make it,
we'll have nothing.

629
00:27:35,190 --> 00:27:36,910
Worst case, we go back to making ads.

630
00:27:37,780 --> 00:27:38,430
Right?

631
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:40,460
Right?

632
00:27:46,020 --> 00:27:46,780
Even if

633
00:27:48,020 --> 00:27:49,540
we go back to that,

634
00:27:49,540 --> 00:27:50,700
we'll still be the number one

635
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:52,190
"Scandalous Couple" there.

636
00:27:53,670 --> 00:27:55,540
Starting over isn't a big deal.

637
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:56,300
Zhou Shui.

638
00:28:00,950 --> 00:28:01,590
Well.

639
00:28:02,020 --> 00:28:03,670
Since we've agreed,

640
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:05,430
I'll ask if she has time
to meet tomorrow.

641
00:28:10,150 --> 00:28:10,980
Cut.

642
00:28:11,300 --> 00:28:12,260
Sorry, sir.

643
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:13,110
Please move.

644
00:28:13,110 --> 00:28:14,060
You're in the shot.

645
00:28:14,060 --> 00:28:14,870
Sorry.

646
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:15,740
Thank you.

647
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:26,950
What are you shooting?

648
00:28:27,150 --> 00:28:27,980
A short film?

649
00:28:27,980 --> 00:28:29,910
Yes. We're making our own short film.

650
00:28:30,460 --> 00:28:32,500
We're going to submit it to Beijing

651
00:28:32,740 --> 00:28:34,460
for the coming script competition.

652
00:28:36,150 --> 00:28:37,220
You're a promising man.

653
00:28:37,500 --> 00:28:38,300
Good luck.

654
00:28:38,500 --> 00:28:39,300
Thank you, sir.

655
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:40,540
Don't call me that.

656
00:28:40,860 --> 00:28:42,430
I graduated from the film school.

657
00:28:42,430 --> 00:28:43,590
I'm your senior.

658
00:28:43,670 --> 00:28:44,500
Senior?

659
00:28:44,950 --> 00:28:46,390
Are you making movies now too?

660
00:28:58,590 --> 00:29:00,110
Sir, we're all set.

661
00:29:00,220 --> 00:29:01,300
All right, let's start.

662
00:29:18,020 --> 00:29:18,780
Come in.

663
00:29:24,390 --> 00:29:25,950
Director Zhou, Director Dai.

664
00:29:26,500 --> 00:29:28,390
Have you made a decision?

665
00:29:29,460 --> 00:29:30,780
If you're not using our script,

666
00:29:30,780 --> 00:29:32,430
we'll quit this production.

667
00:29:32,570 --> 00:29:34,020
We don't need our names on it either.

668
00:29:35,500 --> 00:29:37,020
And you, Director Zhou?

669
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:41,220
We'll hand everything over properly
before we leave.

670
00:29:42,110 --> 00:29:43,350
We don't delay your production.

671
00:29:50,430 --> 00:29:51,260
Impressive!

672
00:29:52,190 --> 00:29:54,500
That's the spirit of young people.

673
00:29:55,300 --> 00:29:56,430
No compromise. No surrender.

674
00:29:56,430 --> 00:29:57,460
No fear of power.

675
00:29:57,460 --> 00:29:59,700
Move forward together,
holding on to each other.

676
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:02,260
You two have truly impressed me.

677
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:03,540
Come and sit.

678
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:04,390
It's fine. Ms. Chao.

679
00:30:04,390 --> 00:30:05,430
Come on. Have a seat.

680
00:30:05,740 --> 00:30:06,590
I'm sorry.

681
00:30:06,590 --> 00:30:08,390
I've been too busy lately.

682
00:30:08,390 --> 00:30:10,060
I forgot to ask.

683
00:30:10,460 --> 00:30:12,700
Have you been paid your director fees?

684
00:30:13,190 --> 00:30:13,910
Well.

685
00:30:13,910 --> 00:30:14,540
Not yet.

686
00:30:14,700 --> 00:30:15,300
Right.

687
00:30:15,870 --> 00:30:17,740
What's wrong with Biao?

688
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:19,590
Anyway, don't worry.

689
00:30:19,670 --> 00:30:21,700
I'll make sure you get paid.

690
00:30:22,060 --> 00:30:22,540
Besides,

691
00:30:22,540 --> 00:30:23,460
I'll do my best

692
00:30:23,460 --> 00:30:25,740
to keep your names in the credits.

693
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:27,300
To be honest,

694
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:28,540
your script

695
00:30:28,540 --> 00:30:30,020
is pretty well-written.

696
00:30:30,540 --> 00:30:32,190
It has warmth and emotion.

697
00:30:32,430 --> 00:30:33,780
But it's too artistic.

698
00:30:33,950 --> 00:30:35,540
It doesn't suit my style.

699
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:36,590
How about this?

700
00:30:36,590 --> 00:30:37,460
I can introduce it

701
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:39,110
to other production companies

702
00:30:39,300 --> 00:30:39,910
and send them

703
00:30:39,910 --> 00:30:41,110
the script.

704
00:30:42,260 --> 00:30:43,910
Have you booked your flights?

705
00:30:43,950 --> 00:30:45,460
I can get you business class tickets.

706
00:30:45,460 --> 00:30:46,670
It's all right, Ms. Chao.

707
00:30:47,150 --> 00:30:49,350
We can afford that.

708
00:30:49,630 --> 00:30:50,500
No.

709
00:30:50,950 --> 00:30:52,150
I insist.

710
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:54,590
Let me show you my love.

711
00:30:55,670 --> 00:30:56,670
Love?

712
00:30:57,260 --> 00:30:57,870
For us?

713
00:30:58,020 --> 00:30:58,780
Because both of you

714
00:30:58,780 --> 00:31:00,670
remind me of my younger days.

715
00:31:01,050 --> 00:31:02,430
They wanted me to change my script,

716
00:31:02,700 --> 00:31:04,190
but I refused.

717
00:31:04,390 --> 00:31:05,670
In the end, I quit.

718
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:07,300
Guess what?

719
00:31:07,300 --> 00:31:08,190
The producer

720
00:31:08,190 --> 00:31:10,300
spread words saying he'd blacklist me.

721
00:31:10,980 --> 00:31:12,980
I couldn't get work for years.

722
00:31:13,260 --> 00:31:14,110
Ms. Chao,

723
00:31:14,110 --> 00:31:15,830
if we leave today,

724
00:31:15,950 --> 00:31:17,910
will you blacklist us too?

725
00:31:18,150 --> 00:31:19,150
Of course not.

726
00:31:19,300 --> 00:31:20,630
I've been in your shoes.

727
00:31:20,630 --> 00:31:22,190
I'm on your side.

728
00:31:23,980 --> 00:31:26,350
What are you planning after going back?

729
00:31:29,670 --> 00:31:31,300
We'll make ads.

730
00:31:31,870 --> 00:31:33,060
Ads?

731
00:31:34,390 --> 00:31:37,870
You're a film director now.

732
00:31:41,150 --> 00:31:42,060
Thank you, Ms. Chao.

733
00:31:42,390 --> 00:31:43,670
We should get going.

734
00:31:43,670 --> 00:31:45,150
We haven't packed our things.

735
00:31:45,190 --> 00:31:46,540
No rush.

736
00:31:46,670 --> 00:31:47,780
Stay a little longer.

737
00:31:47,870 --> 00:31:48,780
Let me make you coffee.

738
00:31:48,780 --> 00:31:49,700
No thanks, Ms. Chao.

739
00:31:49,870 --> 00:31:50,590
It's fine.

740
00:31:50,590 --> 00:31:52,260
My coffee tastes really good.

741
00:31:52,260 --> 00:31:53,590
Come. Sit down.

742
00:31:56,350 --> 00:31:57,500
You know,

743
00:31:57,630 --> 00:32:00,540
the first time I had coffee,

744
00:32:00,740 --> 00:32:03,020
I was eighteen.

745
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:04,780
At that time,

746
00:32:05,260 --> 00:32:06,670
my husband and I

747
00:32:06,670 --> 00:32:10,430
just moved to the big city.

748
00:32:10,430 --> 00:32:10,980
He said,

749
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:13,540
"We have to try real coffee."

750
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:14,700
And guess what?

751
00:32:15,740 --> 00:32:17,110
It was so bitter.

752
00:32:17,300 --> 00:32:17,980
He said

753
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:19,390
it was ten thousand times worse than

754
00:32:19,390 --> 00:32:20,830
the grass jelly from our hometown.

755
00:32:24,540 --> 00:32:25,540
Director Zhou.

756
00:32:26,390 --> 00:32:26,830
Actually,

757
00:32:26,830 --> 00:32:28,670
when I first saw you,

758
00:32:28,870 --> 00:32:30,460
I thought you looked like my husband.

759
00:32:34,980 --> 00:32:35,830
Director Dai,

760
00:32:35,980 --> 00:32:37,630
I'm sure you know
what I'm talking about.

761
00:32:38,190 --> 00:32:39,700
Is Director Zhou the most talented

762
00:32:39,700 --> 00:32:41,220
director you know?

763
00:32:46,190 --> 00:32:47,980
I think my husband is.

764
00:32:48,350 --> 00:32:49,870
When he made his first movie,

765
00:32:49,910 --> 00:32:51,230
he was only in his early twenties.

766
00:32:52,350 --> 00:32:53,980
He almost won a big award.

767
00:32:54,830 --> 00:32:57,060
He was a director,
and I was the scriptwriter.

768
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:58,220
We were the golden couple

769
00:32:58,220 --> 00:32:59,910
in the industry back in the day.

770
00:33:00,950 --> 00:33:01,590
Ms. Chao,

771
00:33:01,870 --> 00:33:03,870
do you need us to follow up
on anything?

772
00:33:04,110 --> 00:33:05,190
Let's not talk about work.

773
00:33:05,870 --> 00:33:07,110
You're just like my husband.

774
00:33:07,260 --> 00:33:08,700
You only care about work.

775
00:33:09,430 --> 00:33:10,870
All he thought about was movies.

776
00:33:10,870 --> 00:33:12,780
He knew nothing about people skills.

777
00:33:13,220 --> 00:33:14,110
In the end,

778
00:33:14,190 --> 00:33:15,740
he couldn't finish his movie.

779
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:16,670
He quit.

780
00:33:16,910 --> 00:33:20,590
I remember he was thirty at that time.

781
00:33:22,220 --> 00:33:23,020
Director Zhou,

782
00:33:24,830 --> 00:33:26,950
you're thirty years old, aren't you?

783
00:33:30,430 --> 00:33:32,700
See? It's destiny.

784
00:33:34,150 --> 00:33:35,190
Anyway,

785
00:33:36,060 --> 00:33:37,150
I finished the movie

786
00:33:37,150 --> 00:33:38,910
after he left.

787
00:33:39,220 --> 00:33:40,780
In fact, I only directed ten scenes.

788
00:33:40,830 --> 00:33:41,780
But that didn't matter.

789
00:33:42,630 --> 00:33:43,780
By the end of the year,

790
00:33:44,190 --> 00:33:46,460
I won my very first award.

791
00:33:47,020 --> 00:33:48,830
That was the start of my career.

792
00:33:48,980 --> 00:33:49,980
What about your husband?

793
00:33:50,870 --> 00:33:51,460
Him?

794
00:33:52,060 --> 00:33:55,870
The last time I saw him
was two or three years ago.

795
00:33:56,540 --> 00:33:58,110
I was at a night market with my friends.

796
00:33:58,430 --> 00:33:59,910
He was running a stall,

797
00:33:59,980 --> 00:34:02,390
selling grass jelly.

798
00:34:03,110 --> 00:34:04,590
There was a long line of customers.

799
00:34:05,390 --> 00:34:06,220
You know what?

800
00:34:06,630 --> 00:34:08,180
The grass jelly he sold

801
00:34:08,690 --> 00:34:10,430
required a complicated
and tedious process.

802
00:34:10,830 --> 00:34:12,710
Chopping the grass jelly

803
00:34:12,950 --> 00:34:14,790
into small pieces

804
00:34:15,100 --> 00:34:18,180
and mixing it

805
00:34:18,430 --> 00:34:19,180
with ingredients

806
00:34:19,180 --> 00:34:19,830
and ice

807
00:34:19,830 --> 00:34:20,980
before serving.

808
00:34:21,830 --> 00:34:23,790
He was alone. No helpers.

809
00:34:25,060 --> 00:34:26,500
He was as stubborn as he used to be.

810
00:34:28,060 --> 00:34:29,500
But his life

811
00:34:29,660 --> 00:34:31,830
had nothing to do with movies anymore.

812
00:34:33,620 --> 00:34:35,020
He was selling the thing

813
00:34:35,020 --> 00:34:36,980
he hated most.

814
00:34:39,060 --> 00:34:40,390
I didn't go up.

815
00:34:40,830 --> 00:34:42,660
I asked a friend to buy me a cup of it.

816
00:34:43,830 --> 00:34:46,390
I took a sip, and I cried.

817
00:34:47,310 --> 00:34:48,020
I thought

818
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:49,980
that was

819
00:34:51,060 --> 00:34:53,140
the taste of youth.

820
00:34:55,980 --> 00:34:57,430
Try the coffee.

821
00:34:57,660 --> 00:34:58,540
It's good.

822
00:34:58,540 --> 00:34:59,660
Ethiopia.

823
00:34:59,660 --> 00:35:01,500
Gesha with the red label
and in small batches.

824
00:35:01,500 --> 00:35:02,500
Try it.

825
00:35:30,100 --> 00:35:31,390
Remember this taste.

826
00:35:31,790 --> 00:35:33,390
This isn't the taste of youth.

827
00:35:34,100 --> 00:35:35,660
It's the taste of maturity.

828
00:35:35,870 --> 00:35:37,430
The taste of success.

829
00:35:42,830 --> 00:35:43,750
Let's leave, Zhou Shui.

830
00:36:13,060 --> 00:36:13,750
Ms. Chao,

831
00:36:14,780 --> 00:36:15,790
I want to make this film.

832
00:36:17,750 --> 00:36:18,580
I can't give up.

833
00:36:24,750 --> 00:36:25,580
Zhou Shui,

834
00:36:27,270 --> 00:36:28,390
are you sure?

835
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:31,660
Are you sure you want to do this?

836
00:36:43,020 --> 00:36:43,830
Let's do it together.

837
00:37:23,030 --> 00:37:24,500
I can't believe he actually did that!

838
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:25,870
That's worse than cheating.

839
00:37:26,100 --> 00:37:27,620
Why didn't you punch him on the spot?

840
00:37:29,830 --> 00:37:31,870
I thought the same thing at first.

841
00:37:32,460 --> 00:37:34,100
But I don't think you were wrong.

842
00:37:34,390 --> 00:37:36,660
She was the one
who chose movies over marriage.

843
00:37:36,950 --> 00:37:38,760
She quit the movie herself.

844
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:40,710
She was the one
who pushed you to this situation.

845
00:37:40,710 --> 00:37:41,500
She didn't mean to.

846
00:37:42,110 --> 00:37:42,870
Everything she did

847
00:37:42,870 --> 00:37:44,500
was to keep us together.

848
00:37:46,540 --> 00:37:48,350
Because of my obsession,

849
00:37:48,870 --> 00:37:50,460
he gave up so many things.

850
00:37:51,790 --> 00:37:52,980
The ad was canceled,

851
00:37:53,390 --> 00:37:54,620
the company was shut down,

852
00:37:55,460 --> 00:37:57,350
and we gave up
on the house and the marriage.

853
00:37:58,750 --> 00:37:59,980
He had no turning back.

854
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:02,460
I used to think that once we had
a house and money,

855
00:38:02,830 --> 00:38:04,870
got married, and settled down,
we were together.

856
00:38:05,910 --> 00:38:06,870
But no.

857
00:38:10,060 --> 00:38:12,230
You can get divorced,
a family can fall apart,

858
00:38:12,550 --> 00:38:13,560
a house can be abandoned,

859
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:14,580
and money can be lost.

860
00:38:14,580 --> 00:38:15,660
But love doesn't.

861
00:38:17,230 --> 00:38:18,870
Love can't be objectified.

862
00:38:27,980 --> 00:38:28,910
And more than that,

863
00:38:31,180 --> 00:38:32,870
being a director is his dream.

864
00:38:34,390 --> 00:38:35,910
He's waited for ten years.

865
00:38:36,100 --> 00:38:37,710
He was only one step away.

